--[[
	PhysicsSpeedBoostUI
	-------------------
	A physics-based walkspeed boost (uses BodyVelocity, NOT Humanoid.WalkSpeed)
	with an in-game UI to adjust Speed and Max Force live, driven by direct
	WASD keybind detection on PC and an on-screen D-pad on mobile/touch.

	HOW TO USE:
	1. Place this script in StarterPlayer > StarterPlayerScripts
	2. Make sure it is a LOCALSCRIPT (rename/insert as LocalScript)
	3. Play the game - a small panel appears on the left side of the screen
	4. Drag the "Speed"/"Max Force" sliders OR type a number directly into
	   the box next to each label (press Enter or click away to apply it -
	   no upper limit, type anything), then press "Enable Boost"
	5. Move with W/A/S/D on PC, or the on-screen D-pad on mobile (auto-shown
	   on touch devices, bottom-LEFT corner)
	6. Drag the panel by its title bar ("≡ Physics Speed Boost") to reposition
	   it anywhere on screen, on both PC and mobile

	MOVEMENT INPUT:
	- W/A/S/D key state is tracked directly via UserInputService, not
	  Humanoid.MoveDirection, so the boost responds the instant a key/button
	  is pressed.
	- On foot, direction is ALWAYS relative to the camera's horizontal facing
	  only - the camera's pitch (looking up/down) is ignored, so the boost
	  never gets a vertical component and W always means "the way the
	  camera is pointed, along the ground," exactly like normal Roblox
	  movement. If no WASD/D-pad key is held, velocity is zero (no movement).
	- On touch devices, a 4-button D-pad (W/A/S/D labels) appears bottom-left
	  and feeds the exact same movement state as the keyboard.

	VEHICLESEAT BEHAVIOR:
	- Sitting in a VehicleSeat normally "eats" W/A/S/D for its own
	  throttle/steer input, and the character's HumanoidRootPart gets welded
	  into the seat, so boosting it directly does nothing useful.
	- This script detects Humanoid.SeatPart every frame: while seated in a
	  VehicleSeat, the BodyVelocity is retargeted onto the vehicle's
	  PrimaryPart (or the seat itself if no PrimaryPart is set).
	- Direction is camera-relative, exactly like on foot: turning the camera
	  left and pressing the movement keys pushes the WHOLE VEHICLE left,
	  regardless of which way the vehicle's chassis is currently facing.
	  This intentionally overrides the seat's own steering rotation with a
	  direct push - it's a boost/thruster, not a steering wheel.
	- Walking on foot still works exactly as before; the script switches
	  targets automatically the moment you sit down or get out.

	WHY PHYSICS INSTEAD OF Humanoid.WalkSpeed:
	- BodyVelocity directly drives the HumanoidRootPart's velocity using force,
	  so it can push the character faster than WalkSpeed normally allows,
	  interacts realistically with collisions/ramps, and "Max Force" controls
	  how strongly it overrides momentum (low force = floaty/slidey,
	  high force = snappy/rigid).
	- The Y-axis of MaxForce is left at 0 so gravity and jumping are untouched.

	NOTE: This is a client-side (LocalScript) implementation. Roblox gives a
	player network ownership of their own character by default, so this works
	out of the box. For a competitive/anti-exploit game, you'd mirror this
	logic in a server script behind a RemoteEvent so the server validates and
	owns the values instead of trusting the client. Ask if you'd like that
	server-authoritative version too.
]]

